              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "3-LI-6",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.993
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Targets of metallic lithium,",
                "enriched to 99.3% mass 6, were evaporated in the",
                "spectrometer target chamber on 5x10**-6 cm Ni",
                "supporting foils. The target thickness, between 10",
                "and 35 microg/cm2 for various targets used, was",
                "determined by measuring with the spectrometer the",
                "energy loss of He3 ions passing through the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The triton energy was measured in the 180 degree",
                "double focusing magnetic spectrometer of 60.96-cm",
                "radius set at 0 degree with respect to the incoming",
                "He3 beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
